<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1625,2010]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,861]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1625,1650]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[497,584,1625,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) yellow with black marks. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[1013,1100,1625,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) pale yellow with six black maculae, two pairs on anterior margin and one pair between ocelli; pair of anteromedian, diagonal black arches; small black maculae between eye and ocellus and posterior to eye. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1151,1697,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) with anterior third pale yellow and posterior two-thirds greenish-yellow; pair of broad black maculae posterior to eyes; small elongate black maculae on median portion. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[692,775,1769,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) pale yellow with pair of elongate, anterior black maculae connected to each other on transverse sulcus. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[789,871,1805,1830]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) brown with costal area greenish-yellow and dark brown stripes on veins; corium with three broad transverse white to yellow stripes bordered by dark brown. Face pale yellow with pair of longitudinal black stripes on frons, converging to median stripe on clypeus; lateral portion of frons with black area; gena pale yellow with black, vertical narrow stripe near posterior margin. Male pygofer with inner ventroapical spiniform process, medially directed. Paraphyses with V-shaped basal plate and apical pair of long and moderately narrow rami. Aedeagal shaft with pair of basilateral hook-shaped processes, posteriorly directed, and pair of similar processes on basiventral portion, anteriorly directed. Female sternite VII with conspicuous central black macula; posterior margin with median, deep trapezoidal emargination. Sternite VIII with semilunar sclerotized plate slightly produced anteromedially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,861]" box="[199,548,260,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
